Flow chart of the electrical simulation strategy proposed.

Initially, the proposed design with the core–shell doping shown in Fig. 1b,c are studied and compared to the conventional cylindrical NW. In this investigation, the electrical characteristics of the QCr-NW proposed were obtained by using the finite element method via the Lumerical charge package36. The computational domain of the 3D charge solver is given by 600 nm, 600 nm and 4530 nm in the x, y and z directions, respectively. The back Ag electrode and the top contact of ITO material were taken as having a thickness of 200 nm25,45. Figure 1b,c show a schematic of the design proposed in the core–shell n/p/p+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
