				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$3\times 3$$\end{document} periodic arrays of conventional and the proposed NW designs in the x–y plane at wavelength of 908 nm. It may be revealed that high Bloch modes42,58 are induced over the periodic QCr-NW design compared to the conventional NW design. Therefore, the optical efficiency of the proposed QCR-NW design is improved compared to the conventional cylindrical design.Figure 3
