				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {cm}^{-3}$$\end{document} as reported in Ref.71. Moreover, the highly doped thickness of the studied designs thickness are small and therefore the diffusion length exceed the active material thickness71. For the axial junction (Fig. 12a), it is seen that the reduction in the J–V curve is nearly constant for both the studied designs. On the other hand, the reduction in the Jsc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
