				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$J_{sc}$$\end{document} of the proposed QCr-NW is slightly increased compared to the Con-NW in the core–shell junction (Fig. 12b). This may back to the increased n-doping radial shell volume of the offered design compared to the conventional cylindrical shell in the core–shell junction. Moreover, the value of Voc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
