				\begin{document}$$V_{oc}$$\end{document} of the core–shell junction of both studied designs was noticeably decreased compared to the axial junction with the reduction in the value of the lifetime. This may back to the decreasing the surface recombination rate, and hence the effect of the bulk recombination is increased compared to in the axial junction72. In addition, the holes minority carriers’ life time is reduced due to the highly n-doped shell layer. Therefore, the higher saturation current density-dependent recombination is increased in core–shell junction49.

