				\begin{document}$$\upmu$$\end{document}s at good and bad passivisation, respectively. In general, the lifetime-depending surface defects have a small effect on the electrical performance compared to the SR effect for the studied designs in both junctions. Table 8 shows the corresponding PCE of the conventional and proposed crescent structure with and without LTD under good and bad passivation. It is evident that the reduction in Pm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
